The Chinese mainland recorded 72 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Sunday, with 41 attributed to local transmissions and 31 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Monday. A total of 388 asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Sunday, and 1,552 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. The cumulative number of confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland is 225,923, with the death toll from COVID-19 standing at 5,226. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 338,934 (64,171 recoveries, 9,405 deaths) Macao: 382 (83 recoveries, two deaths) Taiwan: 3,870,528 (13,742 recoveries, 6,956 deaths)